Create a test file in the tests directory (e.g., ./tests/balance.test.ts). Moonwall uses the describeSuite function to define test suites:

```typescript
  import { describeSuite, expect } from '@moonwall/cli';

  describeSuite({
    id: 'D01',
    title: 'Balance transfer test',
    foundationMethods: 'dev',
    testCases: ({ it, context }) => {
      it('C100', 'Alice should have a balance', async () => {
        const api = context.polkadotJs();
        const accounts = await api.query.system.account('5GrwvaEF5zXb26Fz9rcQpDWS57CtERHpNehXCPcNoHGKutQY');
        expect(accounts.data.free.toBigInt()).toBeGreaterThan(0n);
      });
    },
  });
```

Each test case requires a unique ID ('C100'), a title, and an async function receiving it (test runner) and context (provides the polkadotJs API). The API is initialized by Moonwall before tests run — do not create API connections manually.

